About the latest scatterer update:
I doesn't work with GPP.

Eclipses seem to be fine but there is an issue in the "Atmosphere" section.
A reference to the "SUN" seems to be hardcoded into the scatterer.dll so it produces a massive logspam which slows down the game.

I also tried to changed some configs but the problem persists.

overwriting the dll is enough to trigger the logspam.

 

I'm looking forward to see this fixed

Sooo,

Not sure how my laptop places in the league of potatoes, but here are my system stats:

1. With a basic install (no mods whatsoever), and default graphics settings, everything runs as if were stock. It has been literally years since I played a stock-only game, but everything runs nicely!

2. With only the visual mods included, I notice a FPS drop achieving orbit around Gael. Slightly reducing graphics settings (which I have to do anyway with my usual part mod-heavy installs) solves this.

3. Impatience gets the better of me, and I go ahead and install a selection of my usual mods so I can have a play in sandbox before attacking the system properly in career. I have to remove Scatterer & SVE in order to get reasonable graphics performance, but this is usually the case with a non-GPP install for me anyway.

At this point I refer to the original request @Galileo made for people to run some test on less powerful systems and notice that you specifically requested FPS figures and screenshots. Unfortunately I haven't provided the quantitative data for you and am now far too involved with tinkering with different mods and getting stuck into this brilliant planet pack you guys have made for us!

In summary, GPP gives a slight performance hit on my laptop when installed with the usual volume of parts mods I play with. It is completely playable with a bit of tinkering and compromising.

Sorry I could not be more concise. And thanks for the mod!

3 hours ago, Leafbaron said:

I had one question about the science in the game. are any of the values changed or just the name on the experiment such as Mystery goo high above gael etc.

Science values for Gael and Iota are the same as Kerbin and Mun.  Ceti has a tiny boast over Minmus for the "In Space High" condition, but is otherwise the same.  Other bodies should have values comparable to, but not necessarily the same as the stock game.  GPP has completely different bodies than stock, so don't expect to have the same science return.

Here ae the celestial body multipliers:

Leto 17       15 14 14

The thing that is going to make GPP more difficult than stock is that Iota and Ceti have far fewer biomes than Mun and Minmus.  Therefore there is less total science to reap from those bodies.
